On Fri, Jul 10, 2015 at 12:17:57AM -0700, Seth wrote:
> I actually appreciate content posted in message, get tired of having to  
> fire up a browser for links. Also every click on a browser link is a  
> potential attack whereas plain-text in an email is not.

Normally I'd agree. But in this case it's different imho. Nobody knows
if I read the list posted on wikileaks since the access is tls
encrypted. However, now that the whole list has been posted by mail in
the clear, everyone sniffing on my mail traffic knows that I've got it.

